## üëã About Myself:

Hi! I'm David, and I have two passions: learning and teaching. I love learning about mathematics and computer science, which are the fields that drive me. Teaching is, from my point of view, the basis of progress; it's useless to know if you don't apply it or teach it. I greatly enjoy teaching others everything I know, and this GitHub is a small sample of that ;)

### üìö Education:
I completed my studies in Mathematics and Computer Engineering (specializing in Computing and Intelligent Systems, AI) in 2021 at UGR, [one of the top European universities in AI](https://www.usnews.com/education/best-global-universities/artificial-intelligence?region=europe), achieving High Honors in subjects such as Metaheuristics and Advanced Computing Models.

I completed a Master's in Data Science and Computer Engineering (specializing in Data Science and Intelligent Technologies) in 2024 also at UGR, earning High Honors in my Master's Thesis, a project you can find on my profile under the name [FairTreesAlgorithms](https://github.com/Daalma7/FairTreesAlgorithms). 

I also completed a Master's in Teaching with a specialization in Mathematics in 2023 at UGR, which allowed me to learn better strategies for sharing what I know with the world.

### üìä Experience:
I worked for 2 years (Nov 2021 - Nov 2023) as a Data Scientist and Researcher on a project titled 'Evaluation of Care Needs for People with Chronic Diseases Based on Social and Environmental Determinants Using Advanced Data Science Methodologies.' In this role, I had various responsibilities, such as processing and handling large datasets, using Python, Pandas, Seaborn, Matplotlib, developing Machine Learning models with fairness criteria, inferring attributes with fairness criteria, and analyzing models and results.

I was also a collaboration grant holder (Nov 2020 - Jul 2021) in the Department of Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence at UGR, where my main responsibilities were research on Fairness in Machine Learning and the development of Multi-Objective Optimization Genetic Models for problems with fairness criteria.
